<br>
To answer your question though, I'd pretty much agree with Leifelf.  When a wizard decides to be hard and wastes my time protecting them (Because we all know they drop too damn fast for any other class besides us to save them), they divert my attention from the cleric and chanter (Who are our primary sheep to guard).  Not to mention when any good cleric is in the group, he tries to save the wizard and after I have saved him/her, the cleric's heal goes off and then he gets aggro'd on.  <br>
<br>
To sum my opinion up, wizards who nuke mainly between 2/3rds and 1/3rds of health and average about one nuke per battle make me very happy.  When they decide to yell in group tell "WOOT MOB GO DOWN THE HOLE PROTECT ME!" they really tick me off. <p><A HREF=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=34183>Kalerien Orelias</A><BR>55th rank Half-Elven Knight<BR>Guardian of Druzzil<BR>Proud member of <A HREF=http://www.valiant-hearts.com> Valiant Hearts</A><BR>"Hate is baggage"</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=11939.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=11934.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=11944.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=11944.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11944.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11944.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=